args: The three brides have finished gathering their\nhelpers, which means the battle for wedding\nsupremacy is about to begin!
Let me introduce you to the geniuses who\nwill be putting MY wedding together!
You're using a member of the Ilian Church\nto perform a Hinomotoan ceremony?
Yep! That way, the ceremony will be\na mix of cultures—a wedding that brings\nthe whole world together as one!
Huh. I suppose that does make sense.\nNow let me introduce you to MY team!
I brought along everyone\nI could convince to help out.
We must retreat up the aisle at once!
You walk DOWN the aisle in a wedding,\nAlain. You don't retreat UP it.
I just said I could peel a pumpkin, and\nall of a sudden I'm dragged into this?\nI'm an assassin, dammit!
Your team seems to lack unity.\nAre you sure you can perform\na ceremony together?
Yes, well, now let me introduce\nMY fine assistants!
Waaaaah! I'm so sorry I couldn't\nprotect you, my love!
Er, it's fine. Just please calm down.
I have sent out invitations to everyone in\nthe castle telling them our ceremonies\nwill take place tomorrow.
That will give all of them a chance to vote\non which wedding they think is best.
Then let's make it a day to remember!
Rrrgh! This is NEVER gonna\nbe done in time!
I did not perfect my ninja skills\nfor them to be used like...this.
Terrible! Elisanne is so darn picky\nabout EVERYTHING—I could work\nall night and not finish this!
Er, so how's stuff on your end?
We were able to finish without difficulty,\nbut whether the result is WORTH seeing\nis another matter entirely.
Yeah, it's all just very...by-the-book.\nThere's no sense of individuality.
Mmm. Aoi has the opposite problem.\nHer ceremony is almost TOO unique,\nand I fear none will appreciate it.
It is nothing but ninjutsu from tip to tail.\nShe insists that is Hinomoto's style,\nbut I beg to differ.
Honestly, I am uncertain if her event\neven qualifies AS a wedding.
Sounds like every team's got problems.\nStill, not much we can do about it now,\nwhat with the invites bein' sent and all.
Agreed. People are actually excited for\nthis mad affair, and it wouldn't do to\ncancel the whole thing now.
Aaauuugh! What is the meaning of this?!\nThe food and the decorations are\nnowhere NEAR being finished!
I TOLD you we'd never finish if ya\nobsessed over every last detail!\n...Er, so what's the plan now?
*sigh* I don't know. At this rate,\nwe won't just lose—we'll actually\nend up disappointing everyone.
Why do you two look so flustered?
I worked really hard to create an ideal\nceremony, but it's...it's BORING!

And I went too far in the other direction
and made it all about my style. Now it
just looks like I'm hosting a freakin'
ninja tournament!
If it makes you feel better, I was far too\nmeticulous in my planning, and my\nceremony is nowhere near finished.
It sounds as if we are all in trouble.\nThe question, then, is what we do.
Maybe you should just stop competing\nalready! I mean, DUH!
Then my fated love won't have to\npretend to marry any of you harpies!
Instead of competing against each other,\nwe can work together to create ONE\nceremony everyone will enjoy!
Which will let each of us make up for\nthe other's weaknesses!
Even if we can't give people the\ncompetition they were promised,\nwe can at least entertain them.
It is not too late to save this. Come on!
Yeah, that's right! You all just go! Shoo!\n...Er, I GUESS this worked out for me?
And so, the time comes for the ceremony...
Honestly, this is like dealing with children.\nWho makes a contest out of MARRIAGE?

RIGHT?! I'm personally hoping they'll
start fighting and rolling on the ground
and pulling each other's hair or whatever.
That would be the BEST.
The people are starting to gather.\nLet's see what they can do, mmm?
Attention, everyone! Cease your talking,\nunless you wish to feel the Loving Hand!
The event will begin shortly, and I, Estelle,\nwill be your master of ceremonies.
And me! ...Er, Curran. Now let's have\nsome applause for today's happy brides!
...Huh? Why are they holding hands?\nWHERE'S MY HAIR PULLING?!
May we have a moment of your time,\neveryone?
You were all invited here to watch three\nwedding ceremonies and choose your\nfavorite from among them.
However, we were too immature as brides\nto live up to our promise, and for this,\nwe are truly sorry.
But not wanting all of you to go home\ndisappointed, we decided to join forces.
Together, we've created one ceremony\nthat combines all of our ideals!
It may not be what you were promised,\nbut we hope you enjoy it all the same.
The idea of a competition had me worried,\nbut they all look super happy.
Yes, this sounds MUCH more fun.
Th-then will all of the brides\nplease step forward?
Er, yes. Right then. Do you promise to\nbe good friends, in sickness and health,\nfor as long as you all shall live?
Whew! I'm glad that all worked out.
As am I. Ricardt may have fainted,\nbut everyone else seemed to quite\nenjoy themselves.
I enjoyed myself, too—and also\nlearned something along the way.
Agreed. We should probably hold off on\nwedding plans until we have a better\nunderstanding of love in general.
The whole concept of competing over\nthis was silly to begin with, yet in my\nstubbornness, I would not let it go.
We were all immature as both people\nand brides, and only able to do a proper\njob when we joined forces.
But I'm going to train really hard\nand change that!
As am I—and I believe this escapade\nwas a perfect first step.
So let's keep working together\nto better ourselves!
